            <title xml:id="name222-1"
                   xml:lang="syr"
                   source="#bib222-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">ܫܡܥܘܢ ܟܐܦܐ</title>
            <title xml:id="name222-2" xml:lang="fr-x-bhsyre" source="#bib222-1">Šemʿōn Kēpā</title>
            <title xml:id="name222-3" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib222-1">De Pierre, apôtre</title>
            <title xml:id="name222-4"
                   xml:lang="en"
                   source="#bib222-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">On Peter the apostle</title>
            <note xml:lang="" type="" source="#bib222-1" anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܪ̈ܚܡܘܗܝ ܕܡܫܝܚܐ ܐܬܬܒܥܢܢ ܠܡܫܬܥܝܘ. ܘܠܝܬ ܒܢ ܚܝܠܐ ܕܣܦܩ ܠܡܡܠܝܘ ܦܘܪܥܢܐ ܡܕܡ ܕܐܬܬܒܥܢܢ. ܕܠܡ ܗܿܝ ܕܙܥܘܪܐ ܡܫܘܚܬܢ:</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr"
                  type="prologue"
                  source="#bib222-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">On nous a réclamé de raconter l'histoire des amis du Christ, et nous n'avons pas assez de force pour nous acquitter de ce qui nous a été réclamé, car la petitesse est notre mesure . . .</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en"
                  type="prologue"
                  source="#bib222-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">It was demanded that we tell the story of the friends of Christ, and we do not have the power to fulfill this request sufficiently, for the smallness is our measure . . .</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="syr"
                  type="incipit"
                  source="#bib222-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">ܘܟܕ ܓܝܪ ܒܣ̣ܐ ܒܪܢܫܢ ܩܕܡܝܐ: ܘܥ̣ܒܪ ܥܠ ܦܘܩܕܢܐ ܕܐܠܗܐ: ܘܐܬܓܠܙ ܡܢ ܗܢܿܘܢ ܛܘ̈ܒܐ ܡܫܒܚ̈ܐ.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr" type="incipit" source="#bib222-1" anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">Quand en effet notre premier homme eut avec mépris agi contre le commandement de Dieu et qu’il eut été privé de ces biens glorieux…</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="incipit" source="#bib222-1" anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">For when the first man disdained and acted against the commandment of God, and was deprived of glorious things . . .</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="syr"
                  type="explicit"
                  source="#bib222-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">FILL IN</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr" type="" source="#bib222-1" anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">Et quand l’âme du saint se fut élevée, Marcellus s’approcha, sans avoir pris conseil de personne, et il descendit Simon de la croix… Et ainsi fut achevé le couronnement du bienheureux Mâr Simon… Amen.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en"
                  type="explicit"
                  source="#bib222-1"
                  anchored="true">
               <quote defective="false">And when the soul of the saint arose, Marcellus approached, without having been advised by anyone. He brought Simeon down from the cross . . . and in this way the crowning of Mar Simon was completed.</quote>
            </note>
            <note type="editions" anchored="true">
               <bibl source="#bib222-1" default="false" status="draft">
                  <author>Bedjan, P.</author>
                  <title>AMS 1</title>
                  <citedRange>p. 1-33, </citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </note>
